article.headline: Loyola, Md. 75, Delaware 63
article.story: BALTIMORE (AP) -- Gerald Brown came off the bench to score a team-high 22 points, and Loyola defeated Delaware 75-63 Wednesday night. Delaware, which was behind 17 points at halftime, saw its record fall to 0-5. Josko Alujevic added 12 points and nine rebounds for Loyola (3-2). Brett Harvey contributed 11 points, and Shane James had nine assists for the Greyhounds. Zaire Taylor scored a game-high 30 points for Delaware. Twenty-three of those points came in the second half. Herb Courtney grabbed a team-high eight rebounds.
